deck: Member of the ad hoc Paranormal Probe Program Investigation Team.
description:
Origin

Dr. Martin is a university accredited scientist that was appointed to lead the ad hoc Paranormal Probe Investigation Team.

Creation

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by Marc Silvestri.

Major Story Arcs

During the events of Inferno, Dr. Martin leads his team to the top of the Empire State Building (to the Rainbow Room restaurant) to run diagnostics. The going theory is that the building is growing due to some paranormal activity. Dr. Martin cannot believe that the building is growing and gets into a heated argument with Dr. Snodgrass. This argument infringes upon Havok and Madelyne Pryor's date and the ire of the restaurant's management gets the team kicked out. As the team enters the elevator, the walls produce demons, which kill Dr. Martin and his team.
name: Dr. Martin

deck: Gumbo is one of several main characters from Charlton's Hillbilly Comics. He is billed as "The Screwball O' Th' Hills".
description:
Gumbo lives in the fictional town of Shootin' Creek. His best gal's name is Honeydew Crawfisher, the daughter of the local sheriff, L.P. Crawfisher. Gumbo is well liked by everyone in Shootin' Creek due to his screwball sense of humor and good-natured personality. Even cranky ol' Sheriff Crawfisher admits to liking him once when it appears that Gumbo has died, even though the two don't usually see eye to eye.

In his first appearance, Gumbo attempted to help L.P. Crawfisher with his campaign to be reelected sheriff in order to impress Honeydew. Gumbo did more harm than good at first, but ultimately it was due to him that Sheriff Crawfisher won the election.

Gumbo has great skills in tracking and detection due to having taken a corespondance course for detectives. He is also an expert fighter. His favorite wrestler was Handsome Bill, until he found out Bill was a phony.

Gumbo may be slightly dim, but he's smart enough to know when rich folks are making fun of him and turn it around on them.

Gumbo almost always can be seen wearing his trademark outfit of white, button-down shirt with patches on the elbows, black vest, blue jeans with patches on the knees, and of course his coonskin cap with a feather in it, which he's worn since he was a kid.
name: Gumbo Galahad

deck: Earth-10 version of Aquaman and member of the New Reichsmen
description:
Origin

An Atlantean member of the New Reichsmen from Earth-10.

Creation

Underwaterman was created by Grant Morrison and Jim Lee. His first full appearance was in The Multiversity: Mastermen #1.

History

Final Crisis: Secret Files

Underwaterman is first mentioned in this issue, as part of the Secret Files Sketchbook.

The Multiversity: Mastermen

Underwaterman is seen as part of the Nerw Reichsmen, the Nazi Justice League analogue of Earth-10. It's revealed that Underwaterman is an Atlantean and that his people fought against the Nazis during the war, destroying many of their U-Boats, before finaly joining them. The SS believed Atlanteans to be the root of the Aryan race.

His fate after the destruction of the Eagle's Nest, the satelite headquarters of the New Reichsmen, remains unknown.

Powers & Abilities

Not all of Underwaterman's powers have been revealed, but some mostly resemble Aquaman's powers.

Superhuman Durability

Underwaterman has twice survived point blank explosions from the Human Bomb.

Underwater Adaptation

He can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep. He can also function on land normally.

Longevity

He is long lived, and has been around since the war.

Experienced Warrior

He has long experience at war and participated in attacks against German U-Boats. He has also been a member of the team that defeated this universe's versions of Starro and Kanjar Ro.

Weapons and Equipment

Armored Atlantean Suit

He wears a more heavily armored version of Aquaman's distinct orange scale mail shirt. The gloves are metalic, made from an unknwn material.
name: Underwaterman
